{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":8000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you\nso much, Prime Minister,"},{"time":10405,"text":"that was both fascinating\nand quite inspiring."},{"time":12620,"text":"So, you're calling for a global ethic."},{"time":16000,"text":"Would you describe that\nas global citizenship?"},{"time":20000,"text":"Is that an idea that you believe in,\nand how would you define that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":23215,"text":"Gordon Brown: It is\nabout global citizenship"},{"time":25365,"text":"and recognizing\nour responsibilities to others."},{"time":27586,"text":"There is so much to do\nover the next few years"},{"time":31000,"text":"that is obvious to so many of us"},{"time":34000,"text":"to build a better world."},{"time":36176,"text":"And there is so much shared sense\nof what we need to do,"},{"time":40566,"text":"that it is vital\nthat we all come together."},{"time":42596,"text":"But we don't necessarily have\nthe means to do so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45322,"text":"So there are challenges to be met."},{"time":47560,"text":"I believe the concept\nof global citizenship"},{"time":50000,"text":"will simply grow out of people talking\nto each other across continents."},{"time":54000,"text":"But of course the task\nis to create the institutions"},{"time":56458,"text":"that make that global society work."},{"time":58418,"text":"But I don't think we should underestimate"},{"time":60403,"text":"the extent to which\nmassive changes in technology"},{"time":63000,"text":"make possible the linking up\nof people across the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66209,"text":"CA: But people get excited\nabout this idea of global citizenship,"},{"time":70000,"text":"but then they get confused a bit again"},{"time":72000,"text":"when they start thinking about patriotism,"},{"time":74024,"text":"and how to combine these two."},{"time":75762,"text":"I mean, you're elected as Prime Minister"},{"time":78000,"text":"with a brief to bat for Britain."},{"time":81316,"text":"How do you reconcile the two things?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84921,"text":"GB: Well, of course national identity\nremains important."},{"time":87922,"text":"But it's not at the expense of people\naccepting their global responsibilities."},{"time":91662,"text":"And I think one\nof the problems of recession"},{"time":94740,"text":"is that people become more protectionist,"},{"time":97867,"text":"they look in on themselves,"},{"time":99676,"text":"they try to protect their own nation,"},{"time":102000,"text":"perhaps at the expense of other nations."},{"time":105272,"text":"When you actually look\nat the motor of the world economy,"},{"time":108000,"text":"it cannot move forward"},{"time":109761,"text":"unless there is trade\nbetween the different countries."},{"time":112680,"text":"And any nation that would become\nprotectionist over the next few years"},{"time":116219,"text":"would deprive itself of the chance\nof getting the benefits"},{"time":119000,"text":"of growth in the world economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121100,"text":"So, you've got to have\na healthy sense of patriotism;"},{"time":124362,"text":"that's absolutely important."},{"time":125766,"text":"But you've got to realize\nthat this world has changed fundamentally,"},{"time":129076,"text":"and the problems we have cannot be solved\nby one nation and one nation alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"CA: Well, indeed."},{"time":134161,"text":"But what do you do\nwhen the two come into conflict"},{"time":137500,"text":"and you're forced to make a decision"},{"time":139525,"text":"that either is in Britain's interest,\nor the interest of Britons,"},{"time":144000,"text":"or citizens elsewhere in the world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146383,"text":"GB: Well I think we can persuade people"},{"time":148410,"text":"that what is necessary\nfor Britain's long-term interests,"},{"time":152000,"text":"what is necessary\nfor America's long-term interests,"},{"time":154453,"text":"is proper engagement\nwith the rest of the world,"},{"time":156763,"text":"and taking the action that is necessary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161694,"text":"There is a great story, again,\ntold about Richard Nixon."},{"time":166491,"text":"1958, Ghana becomes independent,"},{"time":170466,"text":"so it is just over 50 years ago."},{"time":172873,"text":"Richard Nixon goes to represent\nthe United States government"},{"time":176888,"text":"at the celebrations\nfor independence in Ghana."},{"time":180331,"text":"And it's one of his first outings\nas Vice President to an African country."},{"time":185000,"text":"He doesn't quite know what to do,"},{"time":186664,"text":"so he starts going around the crowd"},{"time":188437,"text":"and starts talking to people"},{"time":190000,"text":"and he says to people\nin this rather unique way,"},{"time":192310,"text":"\"How does it feel to be free?\""},{"time":194551,"text":"And he's going around,\n\"How does it feel to be free?\""},{"time":197297,"text":"\"How does it feel to be free?\""},{"time":198908,"text":"And then someone says,"},{"time":200034,"text":"\"How should I know? I come from Alabama.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":202205,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"And that was the 1950s."},{"time":208428,"text":"Now, what is remarkable"},{"time":212722,"text":"is that civil rights in America\nwere achieved in the 1960s."},{"time":217000,"text":"But what is equally remarkable"},{"time":219000,"text":"is socioeconomic rights in Africa\nhave not moved forward very fast"},{"time":224000,"text":"even since the age of colonialism."},{"time":227000,"text":"And yet, America and Africa\nhave got a common interest."},{"time":231230,"text":"And we have got to realize\nthat if we don't link up"},{"time":234000,"text":"with those people who are sensible voices\nand democratic voices in Africa,"},{"time":238000,"text":"to work together for common causes,"},{"time":240000,"text":"then the danger of Al Qaeda\nand related groups"},{"time":243000,"text":"making progress in Africa is very big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245000,"text":"So, I would say that what seems sometimes"},{"time":247000,"text":"to be altruism, in relation to Africa,\nor in relation to developing countries,"},{"time":251842,"text":"is more than that."},{"time":253015,"text":"It is enlightened self-interest\nfor us to work with other countries."},{"time":256333,"text":"And I would say that national interest"},{"time":258207,"text":"and, if you like,\nwhat is the global interest"},{"time":260340,"text":"to tackle poverty and climate change"},{"time":262444,"text":"do, in the long run, come together."},{"time":265000,"text":"And whatever the short-run price\nfor taking action on climate change"},{"time":268263,"text":"or on security, or taking action\nto provide opportunities"},{"time":270970,"text":"for people for education,"},{"time":272259,"text":"these are prices that are worth paying"},{"time":274485,"text":"so that you build\na stronger global society"},{"time":277000,"text":"where people feel able to feel\ncomfortable with each other"},{"time":280409,"text":"and are able to communicate\nwith each other in such a way"},{"time":283115,"text":"that you can actually build stronger\nlinks between different countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286480,"text":"CA: I still just want to draw\nout on this issue."},{"time":289000,"text":"So, you're on vacation at a nice beach,"},{"time":292421,"text":"and word comes through\nthat there's been a massive earthquake"},{"time":295652,"text":"and that there is a tsunami\nadvancing on the beach."},{"time":298096,"text":"One end of the beach, there is a house\ncontaining a family of five Nigerians."},{"time":302877,"text":"And at the other end of the beach\nthere is a single Brit."},{"time":306157,"text":"You have time to --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":307562,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":309507,"text":"you have time to alert one house."},{"time":311865,"text":"What do you do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312890,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"GB: Modern communications."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"Alert both."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":325460,"text":"I do agree that my responsibility"},{"time":328929,"text":"is first of all to make sure\nthat people in our country are safe."},{"time":332120,"text":"And I wouldn't like anything\nthat is said today to suggest"},{"time":335454,"text":"that I am diminishing the importance\nof the responsibility"},{"time":338207,"text":"that each leader\nhas for their own country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340627,"text":"But I'm trying to suggest\nthat there is a huge opportunity"},{"time":343803,"text":"open to us that was never\nopen to us before."},{"time":346120,"text":"But the power to communicate\nacross borders"},{"time":348192,"text":"allows us to organize\nthe world in a different way."},{"time":351952,"text":"And I think, look at the tsunami,\nit's a classic example."},{"time":355548,"text":"Where was the early warning systems?"},{"time":358000,"text":"Where was the world acting together"},{"time":360810,"text":"to deal with the problems\nthat they knew arose"},{"time":363069,"text":"from the potential for earthquakes,"},{"time":365526,"text":"as well as the potential\nfor climate change?"},{"time":367647,"text":"And when the world\nstarts to work together,"},{"time":369720,"text":"with better early-warning systems,"},{"time":371433,"text":"you can deal with some\nof these problems in a better way."},{"time":374139,"text":"I just think we're not seeing,\nat the moment,"},{"time":376286,"text":"the huge opportunities open to us\nby the ability of people to cooperate"},{"time":380240,"text":"in a world where either\nthere was isolationism before"},{"time":383241,"text":"or there was limited alliances\nbased on convenience"},{"time":387000,"text":"which never actually took you to deal\nwith some of the central problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390490,"text":"CA: But I think this is the frustration"},{"time":392492,"text":"that perhaps a lot of people have,\nlike people in the audience here,"},{"time":395736,"text":"where we love the kind of language\nthat you're talking about."},{"time":398649,"text":"It is inspiring."},{"time":399682,"text":"A lot of us believe\nthat that has to be the world's future."},{"time":403000,"text":"And yet, when the situation changes,"},{"time":406000,"text":"you suddenly hear\npoliticians talking as if,"},{"time":408806,"text":"you know, for example,\nthe life of one American soldier"},{"time":412000,"text":"is worth countless numbers\nof Iraqi civilians."},{"time":414680,"text":"When the pedal hits the metal,"},{"time":418259,"text":"the idealism can get moved away."},{"time":421626,"text":"I'm just wondering whether\nyou can see that changing over time,"},{"time":427120,"text":"whether you see in Britain"},{"time":429000,"text":"that there are changing attitudes,"},{"time":430684,"text":"and that people are actually\nmore supportive"},{"time":432837,"text":"of the kind of global ethic\nthat you talk about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436431,"text":"GB: I think every religion, every faith,"},{"time":439304,"text":"and I'm not just talking here\nto people of faith or religion --"},{"time":442433,"text":"it has this global ethic\nat the center of its credo."},{"time":446450,"text":"And whether it's Jewish\nor whether it's Muslim"},{"time":449807,"text":"or whether it's Hindu,\nor whether it's Sikh,"},{"time":452664,"text":"the same global ethic is at the heart\nof each of these religions."},{"time":457683,"text":"So, I think you're dealing with something"},{"time":460000,"text":"that people instinctively\nsee as part of their moral sense."},{"time":464815,"text":"So you're building on something\nthat is not pure self-interest."},{"time":468601,"text":"You're building\non people's ideas and values --"},{"time":472602,"text":"that perhaps they're candles\nthat burn very dimly on certain occasions."},{"time":478730,"text":"But it is a set of values that cannot,\nin my view, be extinguished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482902,"text":"Then the question is,"},{"time":484481,"text":"how do you make that change happen?"},{"time":487163,"text":"How do you persuade people\nthat it is in their interest"},{"time":491075,"text":"to build strong --"},{"time":492838,"text":"After the Second World War,"},{"time":494366,"text":"we built institutions, the United Nations,"},{"time":497367,"text":"the IMF, the World Bank,"},{"time":498754,"text":"the World Trade Organization,\nthe Marshall Plan."},{"time":501612,"text":"There was a period in which people\ntalked about an act of creation,"},{"time":505669,"text":"because these institutions were so new."},{"time":507670,"text":"But they are now out of date.\nThey don't deal with the problems."},{"time":510805,"text":"You can't deal\nwith the environmental problem"},{"time":512964,"text":"through existing institutions."},{"time":514463,"text":"You can't deal with the security problem\nin the way that you need to."},{"time":518000,"text":"You can't deal with the economic\nand financial problem."},{"time":520596,"text":"So we have got to rebuild\nour global institutions,"},{"time":523000,"text":"build them in a way that is suitable\nto the challenges of this time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526243,"text":"And I believe that if you look\nat the biggest challenge we face,"},{"time":529335,"text":"it is to persuade people\nto have the confidence"},{"time":532001,"text":"that we can build a truly global society"},{"time":534506,"text":"with the institutions\nthat are founded on these rules."},{"time":537610,"text":"So, I come back to my initial point."},{"time":539951,"text":"Sometimes you think things are impossible."},{"time":541976,"text":"Nobody would have said 50 years ago"},{"time":543953,"text":"that apartheid would have gone in 1990,"},{"time":546000,"text":"or that the Berlin wall would have fallen\nat the turn of the '80s and '90s,"},{"time":550423,"text":"or that polio could be eradicated,"},{"time":552221,"text":"or perhaps 60 years ago,"},{"time":553686,"text":"nobody would have said\na man could gone to the Moon."},{"time":556178,"text":"All these things have happened."},{"time":558000,"text":"By tackling the impossible,\nyou make the impossible possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561416,"text":"CA: And we have had a speaker\nwho said that very thing,"},{"time":565000,"text":"and swallowed a sword right\nafter that, which was quite dramatic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568443,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":569600,"text":"GB: Followed my sword and swallow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"CA: But, surely a true global ethic\nis for someone to say,"},{"time":577000,"text":"\"I believe that the life\nof every human on the planet"},{"time":579686,"text":"is worth the same, equal consideration,"},{"time":582687,"text":"regardless of nationality and religion.\""},{"time":586000,"text":"And you have politicians who have --"},{"time":589001,"text":"you're elected."},{"time":590078,"text":"In a way, you can't say that."},{"time":591517,"text":"Even if, as a human being,\nyou believe that,"},{"time":593627,"text":"you can't say that."},{"time":595020,"text":"You're elected for Britain's interests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597396,"text":"GB: We have a responsibility to protect."},{"time":600000,"text":"I mean look, 1918,\nthe Treaty of Versailles,"},{"time":603300,"text":"and all the treaties before that,"},{"time":605136,"text":"the Treaty of Westphalia\nand everything else,"},{"time":607287,"text":"were about protecting\nthe sovereign right of countries"},{"time":609931,"text":"to do what they want."},{"time":611274,"text":"Since then, the world has moved forward,"},{"time":613550,"text":"partly as a result of what happened\nwith the Holocaust,"},{"time":616551,"text":"and people's concern\nabout the rights of individuals"},{"time":619422,"text":"within territories\nwhere they need protection,"},{"time":623000,"text":"partly because of what we saw in Rwanda,"},{"time":625825,"text":"partly because of what we saw in Bosnia."},{"time":627826,"text":"The idea of the responsibility to protect"},{"time":630000,"text":"all individuals who are in situations\nwhere they are at humanitarian risk"},{"time":634000,"text":"is now being established as a principle\nwhich governs the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637072,"text":"So, while I can't automatically say"},{"time":640715,"text":"that Britain will rush to the aid\nof any citizen of any country, in danger,"},{"time":647000,"text":"I can say that Britain is in a position"},{"time":650000,"text":"where we're working with other countries"},{"time":652000,"text":"so that this idea\nthat you have a responsibility"},{"time":654310,"text":"to protect people who are victims\nof either genocide or humanitarian attack,"},{"time":659612,"text":"is something that is accepted\nby the whole world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661961,"text":"Now, in the end, that can only be achieved"},{"time":663986,"text":"if your international institutions\nwork well enough to be able to do so."},{"time":667588,"text":"And that comes back to what the future\nrole of the United Nations,"},{"time":670756,"text":"and what it can do, actually is."},{"time":673000,"text":"But, the responsibility to protect\nis a new idea that is, in a sense,"},{"time":677000,"text":"taken over from the idea\nof self-determination"},{"time":679656,"text":"as the principle governing\nthe international community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682427,"text":"CA: Can you picture, in our lifetimes,"},{"time":685000,"text":"a politician ever going out on a platform"},{"time":688444,"text":"of the kind of full-form global ethic,\nglobal citizenship?"},{"time":693618,"text":"And basically saying, \"I believe\nthat all people across the planet"},{"time":698310,"text":"have equal consideration,"},{"time":699785,"text":"and if in power we will act in that way."},{"time":702691,"text":"And we believe that the people\nof this country"},{"time":704992,"text":"are also now global citizens\nand will support that ethic.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":707993,"text":"GB: Is that not what we're doing\nin the debate about climate change?"},{"time":711902,"text":"We're saying that you cannot solve"},{"time":714672,"text":"the problem of climate change\nin one country;"},{"time":717000,"text":"you've got to involve all countries."},{"time":718847,"text":"You're saying that you must, and you have\na duty to help those countries"},{"time":723442,"text":"that cannot afford to deal with\nthe problems of climate change themselves."},{"time":727138,"text":"You're saying you want a deal"},{"time":729099,"text":"with all the different\ncountries of the world"},{"time":731234,"text":"where we're all bound together"},{"time":732870,"text":"to cutting carbon emissions in a way\nthat is to the benefit of the whole world."},{"time":737000,"text":"We've never had this before\nbecause Kyoto didn't work."},{"time":741000,"text":"If you could get a deal at Copenhagen,\nwhere people agreed,"},{"time":744885,"text":"A, that there was a long-term target\nfor carbon emission cuts,"},{"time":748120,"text":"B, that there was short-range\ntargets that had to be met"},{"time":751000,"text":"so this wasn't just abstract;"},{"time":752811,"text":"it was people actually\nmaking decisions now"},{"time":755072,"text":"that would make a difference now,"},{"time":756860,"text":"and if you could then find\na financing mechanism"},{"time":759263,"text":"that meant that the poorest countries\nthat had been hurt"},{"time":762000,"text":"by our inability to deal\nwith climate change"},{"time":764120,"text":"over many, many years and decades"},{"time":766000,"text":"are given special help"},{"time":767906,"text":"so that they can move\nto energy-efficient technologies,"},{"time":771000,"text":"and they are in a position financially"},{"time":773818,"text":"to be able to afford\nthe long-term investment"},{"time":776167,"text":"that is associated\nwith cutting carbon emissions,"},{"time":778604,"text":"then you are treating the world equally,"},{"time":782243,"text":"by giving consideration\nto every part of the planet"},{"time":785719,"text":"and the needs they have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787370,"text":"It doesn't mean that everybody\ndoes exactly the same thing,"},{"time":790331,"text":"because we've actually got\nto do more financially"},{"time":792663,"text":"to help the poorest countries,"},{"time":794131,"text":"but it does mean\nthere is equal consideration"},{"time":796898,"text":"for the needs of citizens\nin a single planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800381,"text":"CA: Yes."},{"time":801420,"text":"And then of course the theory\nis still that those talks get rent apart"},{"time":804909,"text":"by different countries fighting\nover their own individual interests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808167,"text":"GB: Yes, but I think\nEurope has got a position,"},{"time":810876,"text":"which is 27 countries have\nalready come together."},{"time":814005,"text":"I mean, the great difficulty in Europe"},{"time":816000,"text":"is if you're at a meeting\nand 27 people speak,"},{"time":818233,"text":"it takes a very, very long time."},{"time":820000,"text":"But we did get an agreement\non climate change."},{"time":823821,"text":"America has made\nits first disposition on this"},{"time":827000,"text":"with the bill that President Obama\nshould be congratulated"},{"time":830842,"text":"for getting through Congress."},{"time":832374,"text":"Japan has made an announcement."},{"time":834579,"text":"China and India have signed up\nto the scientific evidence."},{"time":838000,"text":"And now we've got to move them to accept"},{"time":840868,"text":"a long-term target,\nand then short-term targets."},{"time":843540,"text":"But more progress has been made,\nI think, in the last few weeks"},{"time":846623,"text":"than had been made for some years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":848347,"text":"And I do believe\nthat there is a strong possibility"},{"time":851651,"text":"that if we work together, we can get\nthat agreement to Copenhagen."},{"time":855167,"text":"I certainly have been\nputting forward proposals"},{"time":857430,"text":"that would have allowed\nthe poorest parts of the world"},{"time":860263,"text":"to feel that we have taken into account\ntheir specific needs."},{"time":864330,"text":"And we would help them adapt."},{"time":866331,"text":"And we would help them make\nthe transition to a low-carbon economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870072,"text":"I do think a reform of the international\ninstitutions is vital to this."},{"time":873858,"text":"When the IMF was created in the 1940s,"},{"time":876183,"text":"it was created with resources that were\nfive percent or so of the world's GDP."},{"time":879875,"text":"The IMF now has limited\nresources, one percent."},{"time":882209,"text":"It can't really make the difference"},{"time":883932,"text":"that ought to be made\nin a period of crisis."},{"time":886105,"text":"So, we've got to rebuild\nthe world institutions."},{"time":889000,"text":"And that's a big task:"},{"time":890592,"text":"persuading all the different countries"},{"time":892446,"text":"with the different voting shares\nin these institutions to do so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895515,"text":"There is a story told\nabout the three world leaders"},{"time":898723,"text":"of the day getting a chance\nto get some advice from God."},{"time":903381,"text":"And the story is told\nthat Bill Clinton went to God"},{"time":907404,"text":"and he asked when there will be\nsuccessful climate change"},{"time":912594,"text":"and a low-carbon economy."},{"time":914167,"text":"And God shook his head and said,"},{"time":915778,"text":"\"Not this year, not this decade,\nperhaps not even in [your] lifetime.\""},{"time":919921,"text":"And Bill Clinton walked away in tears"},{"time":923000,"text":"because he had failed\nto get what he wanted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":925120,"text":"And then the story is that Barroso,\nthe president of the European Commission,"},{"time":928769,"text":"went to God and he asked,"},{"time":930250,"text":"\"When will we get\na recovery of global growth?\""},{"time":934619,"text":"And God said, \"Not this year,\nnot in this decade,"},{"time":936978,"text":"perhaps not in your lifetime.\""},{"time":938621,"text":"So Barroso walked away\ncrying and in tears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942377,"text":"And then the Secretary-General\nof the United Nations"},{"time":947000,"text":"came up to speak to God and said,"},{"time":949488,"text":"\"When will our international\ninstitutions work?\""},{"time":952730,"text":"And God cried."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953947,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":957729,"text":"It is very important to recognize\nthat this reform of institutions"},{"time":964399,"text":"is the next stage after\nagreeing upon ourselves"},{"time":968423,"text":"that there is a clear ethic\nupon which we can build."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971634,"text":"CA: Prime Minister, I think\nthere are many in the audience"},{"time":974389,"text":"who are truly appreciative\nof the efforts you made"},{"time":976775,"text":"in terms of the financial mess\nwe got ourselves into."},{"time":979300,"text":"And there are certainly\nmany people in the audience"},{"time":981953,"text":"who will be cheering you on as you seek\nto advance this global ethic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985261,"text":"Thank you so much for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":987216,"text":"GB: Well, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":988549,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}